  "learn": {
    "heading": "Right means bigger",
    "intro": "<p>On a number line, the number farther to the <strong>right</strong> is always the <strong>greater</strong> number. The symbol <strong>&lt;</strong> means \"less than\" and <strong>&gt;</strong> means \"greater than.\" The open side points to the bigger number.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>2 &lt; 7:</strong> 2 is to the left of 7, so 2 is less than 7.",
      "<strong>Ordering:</strong> to go least to greatest, line numbers up left to right: 3, 5, 8."
